<HEADLINE> Slowdown in Dutch Industrial Output Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The slowdown in the
Netherlands' industrial growth rate in 1995 appears to have
continued in the first two months of this year, Statistics
Netherlands reported today.
</P>
<P>
It attributed the weaker growth in industrial output to the
poor performance of the timber and building materials industry
whose output fell some 20 percent due to the severe winter.
</P>
<P>
In addition, production in the chemical industry fell by two
percent and in the rubber and plastics processing industry by six
percent.
</P>
<P>
However, production in the food, beverages and tobacco industry
rose by 3.4 percent, while output in the printing industry went up
by 3 percent and in the metal industry by 2.3 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
