<HEADLINE> Third Go Chess World Championship Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The third go chess world
championship opened here on Tuesday with an entry of 24 top
players from Japan, South Korea, China and other countries and
regions around the world.
</P>
<P>
Among the 24 participants are the top 16 finishers of last
world championship. The qualification round, preliminary round
and the first round matches will be held on April 24, 26 and 28
respectively.
</P>
<P>
After the three round competitions, the top four players will
enter the semi-finals. The venue of the semi-finals are yet to be
decided.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the championship will get a prize of 400,000
U.S. dollars. The first two editions of the championship were won
by two South Korean players Cho Hoon Hyun and Seo Bong Soo.
</P>
