<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-23 16:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Land Blockade Causes Food and Fuel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Israeli warships today continued
to bombard the main coastal road, forcing a halt in traffic
between the Lebanese capital of Beirut and the south.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the southern region was facing serious food and
fuel shortages due to the Israeli blockade which began on April
19.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese security sources said the Israeli shelling hit a
white Mercedez car today near Awali Bridge area, some four
kilometers north of Sidon, causing three people wounded,
including a four-year-old child. The Israeli warships also
shelled the coastal road linking Sidon and the southern port city
of Sour, some 85 kilometers south of Beirut.
</P>
<P>
Some government officials worried that the supply of fuel
would not last long despite the rationing of petrol and diesel
oil in these region.
</P>
<P>
Food shortage was more serious and has caused some refugees in
starvation. In the port city of Sidon, some 300,000 refugees
would consume 200 tons of flour, 75,000 liters of petrol and
20,000 liters of diesel each day.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli blockade of the coastal road also caused shortages
of medical equipment, medicine and children's food in these
areas.
</P>
<P>
"Due to the Israeli continuous shelling of the main coastal
road, few relief supplies could reach the hands of the
refugees. It is the only road that links Beirut with the south,"
Lebanese Economic Minister Yassin Jaber told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Israel has imposed a naval blockade on some Lebanese port
cities since April 13, claiming the move was aimed at preventing
the transport of weapons to the Lebanese pro-Iranian Hezbollah,
or Party of God, by sea.
</P>
<P>
It is the 13th successive day today of the Israeli attacks on
Lebanon since the Israeli Operation Grapes of Wrath started on
April 11. More than 150 people have been killed and hundreds of
others have been wounded. The Israeli attacks also triggered the
exodus of nearly 500,000 refugees, about an eighth of the
country's population.
</P>
<P>
Despite the intensive diplomatic efforts to end the fighting
beteen Israel and Hezbollah, the cross-border exchanges of
gunfire were still continuing today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
