<HEADLINE> Army Day to Become National Holiday in DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Central People's Committee
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) promulgated a
decree today, setting April 25, the Korean People's Army Day, as a
national holiday.
</P>
<P>
According to the decree, citizens of the country will enjoy a
holiday on April 25 and all state institutions, enterprises,
organizations and families in the country are required to hang
national flags on that day.
</P>
<P>
The Korean People's Army was founded on April 25, 1932. 
</P>
