<HEADLINE> Nigerian Education Organization To Hold National </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Council of the
National parent-teacher ssociation of Nigeria is to hold its 20th
congress here to discuss the situation in primary, secondary and
tertiary institutions, a senior association official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, scheduled to start Wednesday in Lagos, will be
attended by all the states and local government branches, said
Laja Idowu Taiwo, National General Secretary of the association.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is imperative because of the "ominous
uncertainties be clouding the educational sector" and of the need
to find a lasting solution to the problems, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, the association has been calling for
a well "packaged educational rescue summit" to reviw the
country's school education.
</P>
<P>
The official flayed the decision by the federal ministry of
education to hold a forum on management and finding of education
on May 17 instead of a summit.
</P>
<P>
The educational system of the country has been inundated with
strikes, closure of school, inadequate funding, examination
malpractices, secret cults and corruption, the official added.
</P>
