KHARTOUM, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Sudan has expressed strong
concern about the ongoing Israeli aggression against Lebanon,
according to a statement released by Sudan's Foreign Ministry here
today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Sudan was closely watching, with deep
concern, the Israeli aggression against Lebanon, which began on
April 11 and has killed more than 100 people, most of them
civilians.
</P>
<P>
It described the aggression as clearly reflecting Israel's
violation of international conventions.
</P>
<P>
The statement expressed profound regret over the silence of the
international community towards the Israeli atrocities in Lebanon
and the attempts of certain big powers to cover and protect
Israel and to guard against condemnation of Israel. 
</P>
