The government occasionally prohibits publication of
security-related news stories on ground that this would be helpful
to investigators.
</P>
<P>
"We want to keep the information from being leaked because we
don't want the militants to use what we have," said Hesham Seraya,
a government prosecutor.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers have run many stories reporting the killing,
which took place in Europa Hotel near the Pyramids on April 18,
and the ensuing investigation. 
