The statement further said that Sudan is renewing its request
in the light of repeated and declarations made following an
assassination attempt on the life of Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak last June, and the ensuing information he revealed in
connection with the attempt.
</P>
<P>
The already-strained relations between Egypt and Sudan grew
sour following the assassination attempt on Mubarak, with Egypt
repeatedly accusing Khartoum of sheltering Egyptian terrorists and
providing them with weapons and other assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
