<HEADLINE> Namibia To Host 36th URTNA Annual Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The 36th General Assembly
of the Union of National Radio and Television Organisations of
Africa (URTNA) would be held in Namibia in May, the South African
Press Association reported today.
</P>
<P>
The URTNA annual meeting would be hosted by the Namibian
Broadcasting Corporation (NBC) in Windhoek from May 8 to May 14,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Windhoek, NBC Director-general Dan
Tjongarero said the conference was of utmost importance to the
continent considering the role of the media to play today and
in the future, specifically, "in promoting democracy on the
African continent."
</P>
<P>
Tjongarero said the URTNA was established with a secretariat
in Dakar, Senegal, in 1962 to promote broadcasting on the
continent.
</P>
<P>
About 200 broadcasters from Africa and Europe are expected to
attend the conference. 
</P>
