<HEADLINE> 5 Killed in Terrorist Attacks in Kosmet, Serbia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and
another five injured on Monday night in several terrorist armed
attacks in Serbian province of Kosovo and Metohija (kosmet),
reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The Information Service of the Interior Ministry of the
Yugoslav Republic of Serbia announced today that the organized
attacks on citizens and police in Kosmet were performed on Monday
between 20:25 and 21:30 local time.
</P>
<P>
Investigation was under way by the Serbian Interior Ministry to
identify and find the attackers, it said.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav news agency Tanjug said unidentified attackers opened
fire at 20:00 Monday at policemen who were on duty in Pec, a city
in Kosmet. Both were seriously wounded in arms and legs.
</P>
<P>
At about the same time, around 10 people in the Serbian
restaurant in the townlet of Decani were machine-gunned by
unidentified attackers.
</P>
<P>
On the Rozaje-Pristina road near Sremska Mitrovica, a police
patrol car was attacked. One woman and one policeman were wounded
seriously.
</P>
<P>
In the village of Stimlje, an unidentified attacker gunned down
a policeman.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Albanians in Kosmet make up more than 90 percent of
the nearly two million local population. They have formed their
own institutions and Albanian-language schools and universities
hoping to secede from Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Executive Committee of the Provincial Committee
of the ruling Socialist Party of Serbia issued a statement today
condemning the terrorist attacks.
</P>
<P>
"The latest armed attacks in Kosmet Monday night show that
Albanian separatist movement has opted for terrorism, which might
prevent a peaceful settlement of the existing problems in Serbia's
southern province," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
