<HEADLINE> Tianjin Development Zone Doing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin Development Zone, the
largest of its kind in China, generated nine billion yuan in
output value during the first quarter of this year, rising 75
percent over the same period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The three-month period saw the zone earn more than a billion
yuan in profits, virtually double over the same quarter last year,
and generate 250 million US dollars in foreign exchange from
exports, an increase of 66.4 percent over the same period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The zone now has more than 1,300 foreign-funded enterprises,
attracting five billion US dollars in overseas investments.
</P>
<P>
It led all the nation's development zones last year with 26.5
billion yuan-worth of industrial output value. 
