<HEADLINE> China Set to Deal with Construction Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China is set to increase
controls on the construction business nationwide and develop
regulations for building projects.
</P>
<P>
This news came at a national conference on building projects
here today, which was sponsored by the Ministry of Construction,
the Ministry of Supervision, the State Planning Commission, and
the State Administration for Industry and Commerce (SAIC).
</P>
<P>
According to sources at the conference, China will have a legal
control drive from April 1996 to June 1997 for construction
projects with an investment of more than 500,000 yuan each.
</P>
<P>
The drive will focus on any illegal actions or signs of unfair
competition in bidding on the projects.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongfu, director of SAIC, said that the drive will also
improve the administering of the registration process, the quality
control investigations, and the authenticity of contracts, while
punishing bribes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
