<HEADLINE> Campaigning Intensifies on Penult Day in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- India's first phase general
election campaigning for 150 lower house seats and 532 state
parliament seats intensified on the penult day today with
candidates and their squads stepping up door-to-door campaigning.
</P>
<P>
The first phase polling will start on April 27 in all lower
house constituencies in Assam, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Kerala,
Punjab, Chandigarh, Delhi, Lakshdweep, Andaman and Nicobar island
and Pondicherry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, polling in part of lower house constituencies in
Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Rajasthan and Tamil Nadu will also be
held on the same day.
</P>
<P>
The coming general elections will be held in six phases from
April 27 to the end of May with the candidates running for 543
elective lower house seats and 911 state parliament seats.
</P>
<P>
The Election Commission has imposed restrictions on
expenditure, which prevented major political parties and fronts
from mounting noisy and showy electioneering.
</P>
<P>
In view of the low key campaign for the general elections, the
Election Commission has also decided to launch a "voter awareness
campaign" through state-owned electronic media to educate the
voters about political parties, candidates and symbols.  
</P>
</TEXT>
