<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PNC Members Issue Open Letter on Change of Charter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Haidar Abdul Shafi, Ziad Abu
Amr, Hanan Ashrawi and Rawya Shawwa -- members of the Palestine
National Council (PNC) and Palestinian Council -- issued an open
letter to the PNC today, setting conditions for any change of the
national charter.
</P>
<P>
The open letter said they could understand the important
reasons calling for amending the charter from purely Palestinian
perspective, for the charter will become more reflective of the
changing Palestinian situation.
</P>
<P>
However, the letter said, "this seems as if we are responding
to Israeli blackmail and dictation and not as a serious price for
the peace process which is based on respect to mutual commitments."
</P>
<P>
"At a time when Israel demands the Palestinian side to
implement specific commitments we find it disregarding its
commitments and the provisions of the agreement signed with it,"
it said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the letter noted, Israel conditions the
implementation of the Palestinian commitments with very cruel
demands and conducts unilateral measures which are creating facts
on the ground which are prejudicing the final-status results.
</P>
<P>
The letter said, "From this vantage point we see that Israel
is required in return for amending the Palestinian charter to
start first by carrying out the following:
</P>
<P>
"1. Accede to the Palestinian people right of self-
determination and establishment of a Palestinian state on its
national soil.
</P>
<P>
"2. The immediate implementation of what is left of Israeli
commitments of the transitional phase which includes the releasing
of Palestinian political prisoners, the opening of a safe
passage and the solution to the Palestinian refugee issue.
</P>
<P>
"3. To stop settlement activities, the confiscation of
Palestinian land and the construction of bypass roads.
</P>
<P>
"4. The commitment to redeploy Israeli forces in the Hebron
area immediately.
</P>
<P>
"5. To lift the Israeli closure imposed on the Palestinian
land and to allow free and unobstructed movement of individuals
and goods.
</P>
<P>
"6. To stop immediately all the Israeli measures that aim at
strengthening the illegal annexation of Jerusalem and its
isolation from the rest of the Palestinian land." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
