<HEADLINE> Welcoming Ceremony for Russian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
presided over a grand ceremony welcoming his Russian counterpart
Boris Yeltsin, at a plaza beside the Tiananmen Square here this
evening.
</P>
<P>
The red carpet was rolled out for the Russian president and his
wife at 6:00 p.m., when they stepped out of their limousines and
were greeted by Jiang. Flowers were presented by two young
pioneers.
</P>
<P>
As the two countries' national anthems were played and a 21-gun
salute reverberated across the plaza's vast expanse, Yeltsin
reviewed an honor guard made up of the three forces of the PLA, in
the company of Jiang.
