bloom and is overflowing with vigor," Jiang said. "The weather is
incredibly beautiful for your arrival -- a good omen for further
advancement of Sino-Russian relations," Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
"We have met many times and can be called 'old friends'," he
went on to say, "I feel very happy about our reunion today."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the Russian president's visit is very
significant and that he is looking forward to the official talks
with him tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that he was very glad to come to China again and
talk with Chinese friends. "We attached great importance to this
visit and did a lot of preparatory work," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that this visit will prove a complete
success, and regrets that his stay in China during his last visit
was short. Yeltsin said he hoped that his next visit to China
will be a bit longer so that he can visit more places.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin presented two books to his Chinese counterpart. One,
"Reform, Development and Stability," is a collection of Jiang's 28
speeches and reports from September 1989 to September 1995 in
Russian. The other, also in Russian, "My Father Deng Xiaoping,"
is by Deng's daughter Xiao Rong.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Jiang hosted a banquet in honor of the
Russian president and his wife.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
