<HEADLINE> Bulgaria's Trade with Other Balkan Countries Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Bulgaria and other
Balkan countries reached 2 billion U.S. dollars last year, a top
Bulgarian business leader said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The local press quoted Bozhidar Bozhinov, chairman of the
Bulgarian Chamber of Commerce and Industry, as saying that of the
two billion dollar turnover, 1.4 billion dollars came from
Bulgaria's exports to the Balkan countries which made up 30
percent of the country's total exports.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria had a trade surplus with all its Balkan neighbors, he
said at a round-table conference on Balkan trade liberalization
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In terms of the value of trade in goods with Bulgaria, Greece
topped other Balkan countries with 620 million dollars, followed
by Macedonia, Turkey, Romania and Albania.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria also hoped to increase its trade with Yugoslavia,
which accounted for 30 percent of Bulgaria's trade with all the
Balkan countries before the imposition of economic sanctions
against it, Bozhinov said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the chamber would urge the government to negotiate
agreements on investment protection and avoidance of duel taxation
with its Balkan neighbors.
</P>
<P>
But tax evasion by Balkan companies in Bulgaria was still a
problem, he noted. 
</P>
