<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Social Service Playing Key Role in Rural Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Farmer Wang Xiangqi was as
restless as ants on a hot pan when the cold wet weather stopped
him from sowing his rice seeds.
</P>
<P>
But a team of agronomists came to the rescue, and now the
farmer from Huanghua Town, Hunan Province, feels relieved.
</P>
<P>
The problem cropped up in the traditional spring sowing season
but Wang and other farmers could hardly sow the rice seed into the
field because of the bad weather.
</P>
<P>
"It was at this time when the agronomists came from door to
door to tell us a few days delay would not affect the sowing of
the improved seeds," Wang noted. "They always come at the right
time when we are in trouble," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wang who has a family of three, has contracted a 0.46-hectare
paddy field, 0.4-hectare orange and tangerine orchard, and a fish
pond and opens a rice-processing mill. He sold 23 pigs last year
and earned a total income of 50,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Wang attributed his success to the help of the Huanghua town
agrotechnique station, which has selected more than 200 rural
households to pilot scientific farming.
</P>
<P>
The town, which has almost 20,000 households and 5,615 hectares
of farmland, has 30 technical stations offering such services as
farm techniques, machinery, power supply, animal husbandry and
forestry.
</P>
<P>
These stations provided farmers with 170,000 kilograms of
improved seeds and 1.2 million yuan worth of pesticides, chemical
fertilizers and small farm machine tools last year.
</P>
<P>
Peng Shuangying, an agronomist and head of the town
agro-technical station, said farmers are realistic, and they
followed suit after seeing the good results achieved by farmers
piloting the scientific farming.
</P>
<P>
According to Peng, every village has an agrotechnician who is
in charge of helping farmers to learn new farming skills.
</P>
<P>
With the spread of new fish-breeding techniques, many farmers
have raised fish output from 300 kilograms per hectare to 4,500
kilograms per hectare.
</P>
<P>
Hunan is a traditional agricultural producer in China.
</P>
<P>
At present, the province has built a number of services
involving scientific popularization, distribution of farm
products, market information, production and supply of improved
seeds, crop protection, farm machinery supply and maintenance and
rural education and technical training.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of scientists have gone to rural areas to
contract for farming, and 20,000 technicians are offering
on-the-spot services to help farmers repair farm machinery.
</P>
<P>
A survey showed that work on 2.04 million hectares of farmland,
or 40 percent of the total cultivated land, is done by machinery
thus freeing about one half of the rural labor forces.
</P>
<P>
Many places have organized tractor drivers to form cooperatives
to contract for field work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
