<HEADLINE> HK Police Seize Heroin Worth 4.25 Million HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Officers of the Hong Kong
Customs Drug Investigation Bureau Tuesday seized 2.15 kilograms of
high grade heroin and 350 grams of No. 4 heroin and arrested two
persons.
</P>
<P>
The retail value of the drugs was estimated at about 4.25
million HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Acting on information, officers of the bureau kept observation
on a car park at Chui Tin Street, Sha Tin yesterday.
</P>
<P>
At about 11:00 p.m., two men were seen walking to the car park
and boarding a private car. When the car was driven to the exit
of the car park, it was intercepted by the officers for a search.
As a result, 1.05 kilograms of high grade heroin and one kilogram
of caffeine were found in a camera bag under the driver's seat.
</P>
<P>
In follow-up investigations, the officers searched a domestic
flat in Hong Lee Road, Kowloon and discovered a heroin attenuating
center in which another 1.1 kilograms of high grade heroin, 350
grams of No. 4 heroin and 15 kilograms of caffeine and a set of
attenuating apparatus were seized.
</P>
<P>
The two arrested will be charged with trafficking in a
dangerous drug and will appear at Sha Tin Magistracy tomorrow. No
bail will be allowed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
