<HEADLINE> Investment in Shanghai's Telecom Industry Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, the leading industrial
city in China, will inject some 25 billion yuan (about 3.01
billion US dollars) into its telecommunications industry over the
next five years.
</P>
<P>
As an important part of the city's ambitious plan for an
"international information harbor", the construction of a
telecommunications network will be greatly accelerated, according
to the "Shanghai Posts and Telecommunications News".
</P>
<P>
The huge investment is to be used in tracing the latest
technical breakthroughs abroad, and developing broad-band,
intelligent and multi-functional networks.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, more network terminals and information data bases
will be put into use along with the expansion of these networks.
</P>
<P>
So far, Shanghai has established a citywide public telecom
system, providing services ranging from digital microwave,
satellite and mobile telecommunications to data delivery. 
</P>
