<HEADLINE> Image Diagnosis and Complicated Diseases Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sanya, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Ultra modern ways of photographing
the human body were put in the picture at a recent National
Seminar of Image Diagnosis and Complicated Diseases held in the
Chinese city of Sanya.
</P>
<P>
Over 300 scientists from the Chinese mainland, Taiwan, Hong
Kong, Macao and a Japanese institute attended the seminar.
</P>
<P>
The seminar discussed recent findings surrounding image
diagnosis, and publicized the new trends in image diagnosis in the
world.
</P>
<P>
One hundred and fifty academic papers presented to the seminar,
including 50 published for the first time, were discussed during
the seminar.
</P>
<P>
Recent years have seen rapid progress in China's image
diagnosis techniques. Some techniques, such as checking for
cerebral tumours and ultrasonic sound screening have been up with
their advanced international counterparts.  
</P>
