<HEADLINE> Gas Exploration Fruitful in Qaidam Basin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sebei gasfield in the eastern
part of northwest China's Qaidam Basin expects to develop an
annual gas production capacity of one billion cu m by the turn of
the century.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, gas reserves totalling 50 billion
cu m have been found in the eastern part of the Qaidam
Basin. Experts put the total amount of gas resources there at
around 700 billion cu m.
</P>
<P>
The local source said that construction has started to lay a
gas pipeline from the Sebei gasfield, with total investment of 300
million yuan. And gas will be supplied to Golmud City in Qinghai
Province, some 190 km away, for power development this autumn.
</P>
<P>
The China National Petroleum Corporation (CNPC) has signed
cooperative agreements with the Amoco Orient Petroleum Company of
the United States to explore gas resources in a 10,000-sq km area
in the eastern part of the Basin.
</P>
<P>
The local source added that a breakthrough has also been made
in gas exploration in the northern part of the Qaidam Basin. A
high-yield gas well newly drilled here showed that this region has
a probable gas reserve of 7.7 billion cu m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
