<HEADLINE> Vietnam Commercial Bank to Issue Mastercards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnam Commerical Bank (VCB)
is scheduled to issue 3,000 mastercards this year and a unlimited
number in coming years, a report here said today.
</P>
<P>
The issuing work will start officially from April 26. This is a
remarkable step in the development of the country's capital market
and is part of the strategy to widen the use of non-monetary forms
of payment, a VCB official said.
</P>
<P>
In the first stage, VCB will issue mastercards only in Hanoi
and Ho Chi Minh city. The card will be issued nation-wide two or
three months later.
</P>
<P>
VCB Will issue two kinds of mastercards-- an ordinary card and
a gold card for high-income customers.
</P>
<P>
The cards will have minimum setting levels equivalent to 1,000
and 5,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The state-run bank expects to issue 40,000 mastercards by the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, VCB has invested 5 billion vn dong
(roughly 450,000 U.S. dollars) in implementing the programme so
far.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the card does face some obstacles. The
Vietnamese people, used to small daily costs, are not familiar
with the use of credit cards and their income is still very
low. 
</P>
</TEXT>
