<HEADLINE> Indonesian Fair to be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will hold an exhibition
on trade, investment and tourism from September 26 to 30 in
Beijing, China, an official of the organizer announced at a news
briefing here today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition -- "Indonesian opportunities '96 -- is organized
by PT. Indo ASEAN Persada (IAP), a company set up to promote
Indonesian-ASEAN friendship.
</P>
<P>
During the exhibition, IAP President Director Susila Budi
Moeffreni said, about 200 Indonesian firms and enterprises will
display their products and services to Chinese people and make
contacts with their Chinese counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Coordinating Minister for Production and Distribution Dr.
Hartorto and Chinese ambassador to Indonesia Zhou Gang both
expressed the hope that the event will further promote
Sino-Indonesian bilateral relations and the economic and trade
cooperation between the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
