<HEADLINE> Reception Marks 35th Anniversary of Sino-Lao Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a reception to
mark the 35th anniversary of the establishment of Sino-Lao
diplomatic ties here today.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC President Qi Huaiyuan and Lao Ambassador to China Ponmek
Dalaloy made remarks at the reception.
</P>
<P>
Qi said in proposing a toast that the friendly cooperation
between China and Laos has scored good results in political,
economic, cultural, scientific and technological fields over the
past 35 years.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Lao good-neighborly relations are not only in the
fundamental interest of the two peoples, but also conducive to
peace and stability in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his conviction that such relations and the
traditional friendship between the two peoples will further
develop through their joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Dalaloy thanked the Chinese government for the
support and aid it has provided to Laos, and said that his country
attaches importance to Lao-Chinese friendship founded by Lao and
Chinese leaders of the older generation. He said he hopes that the
friendly relations of cooperation between the two countries would
be further developed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
