<HEADLINE> Bright Working Future for Tianjin's Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- More than eight out of ten
disabled people in the north China port city of Tianjin have found
jobs.
</P>
<P>
It follows a major drive throughout the city to offer a better
deal for thousands of disabled people.
</P>
<P>
People almost blind with cataracts have had operations to
restore their sight, hundreds of deaf children have been given
special training and a network of special training centres for the
disabled have opened.
</P>
<P>
Now Tianjin has reported marked achievements in developing
welfare services for the disabled, as a result of scientific use
of welfare funds, said officials of the local welfare fund for the
disabled in an recent interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
A working system of welfare funds for the handicapped has been
set up across the city. In 1995, the city raised more than 840,000
yuan in donations and materials for the disabled, with more than
260,000 yuan used in welfare services.
</P>
<P>
Most of the city's districts and counties have established
recovery centers for the handicapped. The city has completed over
8,300 operations on cataract patients, treated over 5,200 cases of
infantile paralysis, and conducted language training with 411 deaf
children.
</P>
<P>
The city has set up 33 schools for various disabled children,
with total number of handicapped students standing at over
8,200. Some 10,000 local handicapped people have attended
practical technical training.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin municipal government also issued regulations on
employing disabled people. More than 66,000, or 83 percent of all
the handicapped who are qualified under the regulations, have
found jobs. Of them, some 20,000 are working with the more than
1,500 welfare enterprises in the city.
</P>
<P>
With the help of the municipal welfare fund, 3,003 out of the
5,000 especially poor households of the disabled are now having an
easy life.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin also established special funds to encourage handicapped
people to participate in scientific work, artistic creation and
writing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
