<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Winery Moved for Polluting Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A 40-year old winery, located in
the scenic Lushan Mountain area of east China's Jiangxi province,
has been moved to a new site.
</P>
<P>
The Lushan Winery boasted more than 10 million yuan in fixed
assets and over 7,000 sq m of factory buildings.
</P>
<P>
The winery is famous for its "Yunwu Tea Wine" and "Osmanthus
Flower Wine", but it also created pollutants.
</P>
<P>
To protect the environment in the Lushan Mountain area, a
famous scenic spot in the country, local authorities decided to
move the factory to Saiyang Township of Jiangxi's Jiujiang city.
</P>
<P>
Removal of factory buildings and workers' dormitories has been
completed, and the original site will soon be covered with grass
and trees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
