LUANDA, -- The Angolan government decided here Tuesday to
suspend its activities in the country's Joint Commission of the
Peace Process until the former rebel UNITA movement shows concrete
measures to comply the peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The World Bank and the International Monetary
Fund (IMF) concluded their week-long Spring Meetings here Tueday
with little progress on plans for debt relief and for avoiding
financial emergencies.
</P>
