WASHINGTON -- U.S. Defense Secretary William Perry said Tuesday
that he would discuss Israeli anti-missile defenses with Prime
Minister Shimon Peres when the latter comes to Washington this
weekend.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. diplomats and their colleagues from the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) have met in New York
to discuss a U.S. proposal to hold four-party talks on the future
of the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A senior U.S. official said Tuesday that the
Clinton administration wanted the 20,000 U.S. troops involved in
the NATO peace implementation force in Bosnia to be withdrawn from
Bosnia by December 14.
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his party
arrived here Wednesday afternoon by special planes at the Capital
Airport, starting a three-day state visit to China, at the
invitation of Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri has said that
progress was taking place in the current international diplomatic
efforts to end a cease-fire in Lebanon, but "an accomplishment
would still need some time." 
</P>
