<HEADLINE> Ningxia Has a Child Arithmetician </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Li Xuewen is a human calculator
- able to add and subtract in just seconds, and he is not yet five
years of age.
</P>
<P>
But his mother says that rapid calculating is nothing new for
her brainy son - he has been doing sums since the age of two.
</P>
<P>
The toddler from the Wudunzi Township of Xingxia Hui Autonomous
Region's Taole County is able to rapidly calculate in his head.
</P>
<P>
Just weeks away from his fifth birthday, Li Xuewen entered a
pre-school class in March this year. His teacher was so surprised
at his ability to do sums in his head, with numbers up to 10,000,
that Li was sent to study in a primary school.
</P>
<P>
Li was also special in the primary school. Asked to add 888
plus 888, he answered "1,776" within five seconds.
</P>
<P>
The same question was put to fourth year students of the
primary school, no one answered within 15 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Li's mother said that Li Xuewen was able to do sums quickly in head
even when was only two years old. He was even faster in accounting
than his elder brother who was a first year pupil of primary
school at that time.
</P>
<P>
Li is able to count at any time, any place and under any
circumstances.
</P>
<P>
His father said they have never taught Li Xuewen arithmetic
before. "But he is especially interested in accounting," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
