<HEADLINE> Philippines, Australia Ink 4 Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines and Australia
today inked four memorandums of understanding (MOU) on technical
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The four MOUs were inked by Philippine Foreign Secretary
Domingo Siazon and Australian ambassador to the Philippines John
Smith.
</P>
<P>
The projects covered by these MOUs involve soil improvement,
utilization of applied phosphorus, control of bacterial wilt on
crops and prevention of bacterial diseases in prawn hatcheries.
</P>
<P>
Siazon said that all these projects are significant in terms of
their impact on rural and agricultural development and
productivity.
</P>
<P>
It is essential for the Philippines to upgrade its capabilities
in agriculture, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
