<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eds: Details added Yeltsin Arrives in High Spirits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
flew into Beijing in high spirits on a fine spring afternoon,
starting a three-day state visit to China.
</P>
<P>
When one of three Russian Il-62 special planes carrying the
Yeltsins landed on the south runway of Capital Airport at 14:40
Beijing time, the Russian President and his wife Naina stepped
down the plane with beaming smiles.
</P>
<P>
At the foot of a red carpet, Yeltsin and his wife were greeted
by Li Boyong, chairman of the Chinese Government Reception
Committee and China's Minister of Labor.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, whose hair was being stroked by a spring breeze,
received flowers from two young Chinese women and two Russian
children.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Yeltsin on his delayed China trip were First
Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovets, Deputy Prime Minister Oleg
Davydov, Foreign Minister Evgeny Primakov, Defense Minister Pavel
Grachev and other senior Russian officials.
</P>
<P>
Also greeting the Russian head of state were Chinese
Vice-Foreign Minister Zhang Deguang and Chinese Ambassador to
Russia Li Fenglin.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later, and escorted by 11 motorcycle outriders, the
motorcade carrying Yeltsin and his entourage drove to the downtown
Diaoyutai State Guesthouse in Beijing where they will stay.
</P>
<P>
This is Yeltsin's second visit to China since 1992.
</P>
<P>
During the current visit Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
Yeltsin are scheduled to hold talks on a wide range of issues
including bilateral relations and international issues of shared
concern.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia are expected to sign a series of documents
governing bilateral cooperation and good-neighborly ties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Yeltsin will later join the heads of state from
Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan in Shanghai to sign an
agreement on the build-up of confidence in the military field in
border areas.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the current visit by Yeltsin will push
Sino-Russian friendly relations and cooperation into a new era.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
