<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Good Neighbors, Friends Along Sino-Russian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- An old Chinese saying goes that
"neighbors are dearer than distant relatives". This not only
expresses the common wish of people on both sides of the
Sino-Russian border, but is also a real depiction of the existing
friendly relations between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Last year, just before Christmas, frontier inspectors from both
sides saluted each other on a cross-border bridge and entered the
office of the director of the Russian frontier inspection station,
talking and laughing.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant-Colonel Li Huizhang and his colleagues from the
Dongning frontier inspection station went to express festive
greetings to their Russian counterparts stationed at the Tavka
frontier inspection station.
</P>
<P>
Director of the border post Aleksander Nikolaevich Banov said,
"Christmas is a festival that we celebrate together with our
relatives and friends. Today it is our Chinese friends and
relatives who are celebrating the festival with us."
</P>
<P>
During China's Spring Festival, Russian frontier guards are
invited to Chinese frontier inspection stations to attend festival
celebrations and watch videos on the rapid development of China's
construction and economy.
</P>
<P>
They said, "Of course, we are happy that the Chinese people
have become rich. Peace is the guarantee for national prosperity
and the happiness of all people."
</P>
<P>
There are increasing exchanges across the border between
businessmen, tourists, students going abroad, government
officials, fashion models, experts, scholars, workers, farmers,
women and children.
</P>
<P>
Once a Chinese customs inspector broke his right leg while
working on an inspection ship. The Russian side immediately rushed
to the rescue and sent him to the central hospital in Khabarovsk
by helicopter.
</P>
<P>
Eight Russian frontier guards donated blood to the Chinese
inspector, who returned to Chinese frontier inspection station
safely later.
</P>
<P>
A Russian official said, "The development of the Far East area
of Russia needs help from China," noting, "of course, China's
modernization drive also needs help from Russia."
</P>
<P>
He added, "We depend on each other to achieve economic
development and the happiness of mankind."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
