<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Laughter Replaces War of Words on Sino-Russian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A friendly revolution has taken
place along the world's longest border, where the Iron Curtain met
the Bamboo Curtain.
</P>
<P>
Two decades of military confrontation between China and Russia
have been replaced by a new spirit of friendship.
</P>
<P>
Instead of war games its sports games, as troops from each side
battle it out in a competitive spirit on playing fields in towns
along the 4,300 kilometer border.
</P>
<P>
The sounds of tanks and troop carriers have been drowned out by
the musical notes of dance ensembles, and the dinner parties have
become place where high ranking officers from China and Russia
meet to share their experiences.
</P>
<P>
Contact between frontier troops of China and Russia have been
strengthened in recent times.
</P>
<P>
Frequent exchange of visits by border troops of both sides have
cemented a friendly relationship between the two great nations in
the world, said Shi Jianye, director of the Frontier Public
Security Bureau of Heilongjiang, which shares 70 percent of the
4,300-km-long boundary line with Russia, the longest in the world.
</P>
<P>
Shi just came back from a tour to Russia at the invitation of
the commander of the Russian Pacific Border District. During his
visit, Shi signed an agreement on maintaining the peace and
friendly relations on the Sino-Russian border.
</P>
<P>
In June 1990, leading officials of both sides reached a
consensus on increasing friendly visits by high-ranking officials
from each other.
</P>
<P>
Since then, exchange of visits by senior frontier army officers
have been on the rise. Border guards of both sides have invited
each other to attend festival celebrations, dinner parties or
cultural activities and sports games.
</P>
<P>
On May 28, 1995, the Russian soldiers invited their Chinese
counterparts to a military sports meeting to mark the frontier
army day. Soon afterwards, the Russian Far East and the Pacific
Border Districts sent song and dance ensembles to perform at
border cities of Suifenhe and Heihe.
</P>
<P>
Enhanced friendship brings peace and tranquility on the
Sino-Russian border and promotes bilateral trade and economic
development, said a Russian officer.
</P>
<P>
Chinese observers deem that the growing friendly ties between
border troops of China and Russia will not only help to maintain
peace and prosperity on the border areas but also be conducive to
the establishment of a partnership between the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960424.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Keen On Joint Ventures With Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan said here today
that Pakistani companies are keen to have joint ventures with
Malaysian companies in the defense-related industry.
</P>
<P>
Director of Pakistan Export Promotion Bureau Azhar A.C.
Chaudhry, who is here to attend the Defense Services Asia
Exhibition (DSA '96), told the press that many of the Pakistani
companies are willing to have a complete transfer of technology
and to assemble the products in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Pakistan has more than 50 years' experience in the
defense industry, he said Pakistan had many things to offer and
its products are of high quality and cheaper than those from
western countries.
</P>
<P>
It is also reported that many Malaysian private defense-related
companies have shown interest in some of Pakistan's military
equipment, including Anza MK-I and Anza MK-II portable
anti-aircraft missile weapon system.
</P>
<P>
Reports quoted some Pakistani officials as saying that
Pakistani companies are ready for technology transfer as well as
for joint ventures between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Reports said Malaysian armed forces are also interested in
Pakistan's 106mm heat-seeking anti-tank ammunition and anti-tank
and anti-personnel mines.  
</P>
