<HEADLINE> HK Container Throughput Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Throughput at Hong Kong's
container terminals dropped for the first time in more than three
years, according to the latest official statistics for March.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Port Department Board (PDB) said that
throughput at the eight container terminals fell 5.7 percent in
March, the first month of negative growth since January 1993.
</P>
<P>
Growth in terminal traffic for the first quarter of 1996 also
slowed down to 1.7 percent, compared with a 10-percent increase
during the corresponding period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The drop in container throughput in March was partly due to the
decline of Chinese exports in the first three months of this
year, according to a PDB official.
</P>
<P>
The container terminal industry currently accounts for 20
percent of the Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
