<HEADLINE> World Record Holder Finishes Third in Olympic Trials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- World record holder Kieren
Perkins finished only third in the men's 400 meters freestyle in
the Australian swimming Olympic trials at Sydney on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Perkins, who ranked only eighth after morning's heats, improved
his heat time by five seconds but still failed to catch Daniel
Kowalski in the final.
</P>
<P>
Perkins was timed 3 minutes 52.56 seconds, far outside of his
world record of 3:43.80 he set at the Rome world championships in
1994. He might miss the chance of representing Australia in the
event at the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Perkins is the world record holder for the 400 meters as well
as 800 and 1,500 meters freestyle.
</P>
<P>
Another Australian world record holder Samantha Riley was
beaten for the third time at the Olympic trials when she lost to
Nadine Neumann in the women's 200-meter breaststroke.
</P>
<P>
Neumann clocked 2:29.65, beating Riley to the second place at
2:31.12. Brooke Hanson finished third in 2:32.23. 
</P>
