<HEADLINE> China to Merge State-level Art Troupes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Culture
announced here today that 13 state-level art troupes will be
merged into 10. The aim of the step is to improve management
efficiency and performance quality, while helping individual
performers earn more.
</P>
<P>
Ai Qingchun, vice-minister of culture, said the Central Opera
Theater and the Central Ballet Troupe will be merged into the
Central Opera and Ballet Theater, while the Central Song and Dance
Ensemble and the China Light Music Society will join to become the
China Song and Dance Ensemble.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Central Philharmonic Orchestra is to be changed
into the Chinese Symphony Orchestra, while a Pingju Opera Theater
will be dismissed.
</P>
<P>
During the reform period, some important financial performances
and cultural exchanges involving foreign countries will be
continued.
</P>
<P>
Ai also added that China is carrying out a professional
examination system involving performers, in a bid to improve
artists' professional skills. Performers who pass the examination
will sign contracts with the art troupes.  
</P>
