<HEADLINE> Rapid Growing Economy in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has reported a gross
domestic product of more than 60 billion yuan during the first
quarter of this year, up 11.4 percent over the same period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The three months saw the city score more than 111.3 billion
yuan in industrial output value, an increase of 14.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
It handled more than 9.6 billion US dollars-worth of foreign
trade during the period, up 15.9 percent, and attracted more than
2.24 billion US dollars in overseas investment, rising 21 percent.
</P>
<P>
It invested a total of 17.4 billion yuan in fixed assets during
the three-month period, up 35 percent over the same period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
Its total turnover from commodity retail sales of the three
months rose 27 percent over the same period in 1995 to reach 28.7
billion yuan, with retail prices rising 6.2 percent last month.
</P>
<P>
