<HEADLINE> Qatar to Invest 14.2 Billion Dollars in Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Gulf state of Qatar is to
invest 14.2 billion U.S. dollars in its natural gas projects in a
bid to increase its revenue.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today from Qatari capital Doha quoted
the Qatari General Petroleum Corporation as saying that Qatar will
totally invest some 27 billion dollars on expanding its oil and
gas sectors, with the gas sector enjoying the lion's share.
</P>
<P>
Qatar has embarked on massive projects to tap its North Field,
the largest single reservoir of natural gas in the world, with
an estimated reserves of some 7.1 trillion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf Arab country is expected to produce some 20 million
tons of liquefied natural gas per year after the completion
of the projects.
</P>
<P>
Qatar, a member state of the OPEC, currently produces 378,000
barrels of oil per day. Qatar's crude oil reserves are estimated
at 4.5 billion barrels. 
