<HEADLINE> Ugandan Defence Forces Pursue rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 24 (Xinhua)-- The Uganda People's Defence
Forces (UPDF) and local people with spears, bows, arrows and
pangas pursued more than 70 defeated rebels of the West Nile Bank
Front (WNBF) on Monday and Tuesday when the rebels were fleeing
Uganda's Arua Town to Zaire.
</P>
<P>
In two battles on Sunday morning, according to a report
reaching here today, 30 rebels were killed and another 11
captured and a big quantity of weapons and ammunition were
obtained.
</P>
<P>
The rebels invaded from Sudan on April 17 through Aringa
county.
</P>
<P>
James Kazini, UPDF Overall Operational Commander in West Nile
Region was quoted as saying that the support given by the
civilians is "exceptionally patriotic."
</P>
<P>
"I have fought wars in Uganda. But i have never seen this
support nor read of it anywhere else. While villagers went in
search of the rebels in spite of the danger to their lives,"
Kazini said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
