<HEADLINE> Romario Picked Up for FIFA All-Star Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian soccer star Romario
was picked up by FIFA for its World All-Star game in July, sources
from the world soccer's governing body said in Zurich, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Under the fixture, Romario who paced Brazil to win the 1994
World Cup in the United States, was pitched to play against his
compatriots in July 14 at the Giants Stadium, New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
Other members in the All-Star team include Jurgen Klinsmann and
Lothar Matthaus of Germany, George Weah of Liberia, Marcel
Desailly of France and Mexico goalie Jorge Campos.
</P>
<P>
Krassimir Balakov of Bulgaria and Kaza Miura of Japan were also
in the squad. 
</P>
