<HEADLINE> Work Starts on Chengdu-Leshan Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province in southwest
China has recently started the construction of an expressway to
link this provincial capital with Leshan, a major tourist city in
the province, the "China Transportation News" reported.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will be 91 km long and have four lanes. It is
expected to be completed by 1998, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will cost about 900 million yuan, 46 percent of
which will be provided by the Sichuan Expressway Construction
Company, and the other 54 percent by Leshan City.
</P>
<P>
An announcement by the government of Leshan says it will raise
the funds from banks and the issuing of bonds. 
</P>
