<HEADLINE> Perkins Makes 400m Freestyle Finals with Poor Score </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- World record holder Kieren
Perkins was out of form anew by booking the last spot into the
finals of the 400-meter freestyles at the Australian National
Olympic Swimming Trials on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Perkins, 22, swam home in three minutes 58.85 seconds, only two
minutes ahead of his ninth-placer compatriot.
</P>
<P>
The heats in the morning was won by Daniel Kowalski in 3:55.40.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Perkins was eliminated from the finals of the
200-meter freestyles.
</P>
<P>
Coach John Carew said he had never seen such a poor performance
by Perkins whom he had coached since he was eight. 
