<HEADLINE> Mass Hunger Strike Planned for Bangladeshi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Jatiya (National) Party, one of
the major political parties in Bangladesh, has announced a program
of "mass hunger strike" across the country Thursday to press for
the release of its jailed chairman and the country's ex-president
H.M. Ershad.
</P>
<P>
Ershad took power in the early 1980s and was forced to step
down in 1989. Afterwards, he was arrested and sentenced to
imprisonment on corruption charges by the authorities under the
Khaleda Zia government of the Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP).
</P>
<P>
Announcing the program at its grand rally here Tuesday, JP
Acting Chairman Mizanur Rahman Chowdhury said that it is the
constitutional right of Ershad to go to his electorate to present
his party's program for the coming general elections.
</P>
<P>
"There can be no election without releasing our leader,"
Mizanur said, urging the party supporters to continue the movement
for Ershad's release and the election campaign simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
He called upon the caretaker government not to create a
situation that might hamper the neutrality of the polls and
threatened of "tougher agitation" for non-compliance.
</P>
<P>
Without Ershad's release, there could not be a free and fair
election, the acting chairman stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
