<P>
They reached the agreement at a two-day third session of the
Sino-Croatian Economic and Trade Cooperation Commission, which
ended here today.
</P>
<P>
Volumes of both direct and entrepot trade between the two
countries have increased in the past two years, according to the
minutes of the session.
</P>
<P>
Firms of the two countries have exchanged visits more
frequently and have cooperated in various ways and fields in the
past few years, the minutes said.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the two sides expressed their satisfaction over
their cooperation in the past and agreed to make further efforts
to create favorable conditions for the steady development of
economic and trade cooperation between the two countries in the
future.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the Croatian officials said they will support
Chinese enterprises in joining the work of reconstruction in the
war-stricken areas in Croatia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side invited Croatian businessmen to take part in
energy and infrastructure projects in China.
</P>
<P>
Croatia is China's biggest trading partner in eastern Europe
with a turnover of about 600 million U.S. dollars in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
