<HEADLINE> Old Polish Zloties to Stop Circulation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Polish banks will be more crowded
as Poles are pouring in to meet a year-end deadline for exchanging
their old zloties for new ones.
</P>
<P>
The national bank announced today that all old zloties should
be withdrawn from circulation by the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
To facilitate calculation and prevent counterfeiting, the bank
issued new zloties in January 1995, chopping five zeros off the
bank notes.
</P>
<P>
The new notes are circulating alongside the old ones but have
so far only accounted for 61 percent of the total currency
circulating on the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
