<HEADLINE> New European Navy Comes Into Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Four thousand troops and 15
warships from four European countries joined forces today in a new
joint navy of the Western European Union (WEU).
</P>
<P>
Euromarfor, a joint operation between Spain, France, Italy and
Portugal, will patrol mainly in Mediterranean areas, but could be
deployed to other regions if requested by NATO or the United
Nations, its commander, Spanish Admiral Manuel Acedo Manteola,
said today.
</P>
<P>
He said the navy, which will focus on humanitarian missions,
could be dispatched to the former Yugoslav areas if needed.
</P>
<P>
Euromarfor will leave for Italian waters to take part in a
joint military exercise, "Eolo 96" this weekend.
</P>
<P>
The WEU is a 10-nation European intergovernmental security and
defense alliance. 
</P>
