<HEADLINE> Work Starts on Handan-Jinan Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The construction of the
Handan-Jinan Railway, a key project of the Ninth Five-Year Plan
period (1996-2000), has been kicked off.
</P>
<P>
The line will run 231 km from Handan City in Hebei Province on
the Beijing-Guangzhou Railway to Yancheng City on the
Beijing-Shanghai Railway. It will open a new channel for the
transport of coal from Shanxi Province to Shandong Province and
other parts of east China.
</P>
<P>
The project will cost about 3.04 billion yuan and is expected
to be completed by 1998. 
</P>
