<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Great Success Achieved in Disarmament in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The German government said great
success was achieved in disarmament in 1995 with 182 nations
agreeing on an indefinite extension of the Nuclear
Nonproliferation Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The German cabinet passed today the 1995 disarmament report
submitted by the Foreign Ministry, which says 30 European
countries destroyed 50,000 tanks, armored personnel carriers,
artillery batteries, fighters and helicopters last year. This was
the first time in European history that such a big achievement had
been made in disarmament.
</P>
<P>
The German government announced a complete ban on using
anti-personnel landmines, paving the way for future negotiations,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
It said Germany will continue leading efforts to reach
agreements on chemical weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
