<HEADLINE> Capriati Recruited in US Federation Cup Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Former Olympic champion
Jennifer Capriati was recruited into the U.S. Federation Cup
tennis squad as both Chanda Rubin and Lindsay Davenport withdraw
due to wrist injuries, reports here said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Capriati, who failed to show up in most of past two years, will
join Gigi Gernandez and Mary Joe Fernandez to play in Salzburg,
Austria this weekend.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Fernandez was rated 14th with Fernandez ranked 67th
and Capriati 104th.
</P>
<P>
Davenport who ranked 10th in the world, dropped out with a left
wrist injury while sixth-ranked Rubin skipped due to a sore right
wrist.
</P>
<P>
Capriati, the 1992 Olympic champion, recorded 9-1 in Federation
Cup matches in 1990 and 1991. Later, she quit the sport and only
returned to the court early this year.
</P>
<P>
Against Austria, the United States which lost to Spain in the
finals of last year, boasted six straight wins in a row. 
</P>
