<HEADLINE> Burkina Faso's President Ends Visit to Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- President of Burkina Faso Blaise
Compaore ended his three-day official visit to Libya today, with
both countries expressing satisfaction with their relations, the
Libyan news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a joint press communique issued at the end of the visit, the
two sides voiced concern over continuing conflicts among some
African states, particularly in Somalia, Rwanda, Burundi, Liberia
and Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The communique called for resolving these conflicts within the
African framework and redoubling efforts to tackle Africa's
economic problems.
</P>
<P>
The two sides spelled out the necessity of prompting the
Organization of African Unity to undertake its duties in full, the
joint communique said. 
