<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanon Calls on GA to Condemn, Punish Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese President Elias
Hraoui on Tuesday called upon the U.N. General Assembly to condemn
and punish Israel for its crimes against Lebanon, which led to the
deaths of up to 175 people.
</P>
<P>
The president made the appeal in a General Assembly meeting
called by the Non-aligned Movement on the situation caused by the
Israeli military actions in Southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
"We expected the world to help us develop our reconstruction
capabilities. Instead, we come to you today bearing the blood of
our innocent people and bearing witness to our hopes that were
shattered by Israel: that is our faith in international legitimacy
to recover our rights," said Hraoui.
</P>
<P>
"We came here in the hope that we shall all stand firmly and
decisively together against aggression and transgression, against
the heinous crimes that go unpunished," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the Israeli occupation of Southern Lebanon, the
president said that Security Council Resolution 425 should be
implemented so that Lebanese security forces could assume
responsibility for security in the areas of the south and western
Bekaa Valley.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources said that the General Assembly is
considering a draft resolution condemning recent Israeli attacks
on Southern Lebanon and calling upon it to withdraw from Southern
Lebanon. The meeting will continue on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
