<HEADLINE> Bildt, Serb Premier Hold Talks on Future Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The international High
Representative for Bosnia Carl Bildt held talks today in Serb
stronghold Pale with Serb Prime Minister Rajko Kasagic on future
political steps to change the present situation.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, Bildt told reporters the Council of Europe
will help local people living in difficult social conditions to
improve their life. Political problems cannot be more important
than reconstruction aid, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Serbs had been under international sanctions until last
February 3.
</P>
<P>
Kasagic said after the talks with Bildt that cooperation
between the Serbs and international institutions, the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the World Bank would be
successful and that no more sanctions would be imposed against the
Serb entity -- the Republika Srpska.
</P>
<P>
Kasagic informed Bildt about the reasons behind the refusal of
Serb authority to take part in a recent donors' conference for the
reconstruction of Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
"I asked the international community to treat the Serb entity
and the Muslim-Croat federation on an equal footing and to equally
invest in the reconstruction of both entities," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
