<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Edge Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Shares on the New York Stock
Exchange rose today with technology issues leading the way again.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 23.85 to close at
5,588.59, mostly on gains in the blue-chip index's three oil
stocks. The Dow has meandered aimlessly for the past few sessions,
while smaller company stocks have lifted other indexes to new
records.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues led decliners by about 9 to 7 on the NYSE,
with volume totalling 452.66 million shares, up from 394.01
million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite rose 1.79 to 349.60 and the S&AMP;P 500 rose
3.69 to 651.58.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite rose 11.60 to 1,165.10. The Amex market
value index gained 3.36 to 590.73, setting its sixth straight
high.
</P>
<P>
Oil stocks rose with oil prices amid news the United States and
Britain have pushed the United Nations to toughen its negotiating
position with Iraq over a possible oil-for-food deal.
</P>
<P>
Technology stocks benefited from the latest in a series of
encouraging earnings reports that suggest the industry is not as
bad off as was feared earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Digital Equipment shares shot up after the computer maker said
its quarterly earnings rose 68 percent as the computer maker
posted strong sales increases in its storage and server lines.
</P>
<P>
Among other NYSE technology issues, Motorola, Compaq Computer
and Texas Instruments rose. But IBM continued to struggle in the
aftermath of last week's cautious outlook by the company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
