<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Releases Poverty Figures For 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- About 71 percent of Nigerian
households are poor, the Federal Office of Statistics said today.
</P>
<P>
The office said in its publication tagged "The Nigerian
Household 1995" that about 36 percent are very poor while about
35 percent are "moderately" suffering poverty.
</P>
<P>
It said the sectoral distribution showed that about 77 percent
of the urban households were poor and the rate of poverty at the
rural households category was 68 percent.
</P>
<P>
The poverty levels on gender basis showed that 73 percent and
57 percent of men-headed and women-headed households were poor
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The statistics office stated that the larger the size of a
household, the poorer its members. But it did not give the
standard of poverty in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
